                  <p>Dr. Sun Aixin is an Associate Professor and Associate Dean (Undergraduate Education) at the College
                     of Computing and Data Science (<a href="https://www.ntu.edu.sg/computing"
                        target="_blank">CCDS</a>), Nanyang Technological University (<a href="http://www.ntu.edu.sg/"
                        target="_blank">NTU</a>), Singapore. <!--- where he has been a faculty member since 2005. His previous
                     roles include Associate Chair (Academic) from 2023 to 2024 and Assistant Chair from 2016 to 2023.
                     Dr. Sun also serves on the Singapore Data Science Consortium (SDSC) Technical Committee and is
                     NTU's SDSC institution representative. --> He received B.A.Sc. (First Class Honours) in Computer Engineering and Ph.D. from NTU in 2001 and 2004, respectively. His research interests include information retrieval, recommender systems, and natural language processing (NLP). He has published around 300 papers, which have garnered over 25,000 citations and an h-index of 72, according to Google Scholar. His work has earned several accolades, including the SIGIR 2025 Test of Time Honorable Mention Award, the Best Student Paper Award at the IEEE International Conference on Services Computing in 2020, and a Best Student Paper Honorable Mention at SIGIR 2016. </p>

                  <p>Dr. Sun is an associate editor for ACM Transactions on Information Systems (TOIS), ACM Transactions
                     on Recommender Systems (TORS), ACM Transactions on Intelligent Systems and Technology (TIST), and
                     an editorial board member of the Journal of the Association for Information Science and Technology
                     (JASIST). He has held significant conference roles, including Doctoral Consortium co-chair for
                     WSDM2023, demonstration track co-chair for SIGIR2020, ICDM2018, and CIKM2017, PC co-chair for
                     AIRS2019, and general chair for ADMA2017.  
                     <!-- He has also contributed to the best short paper committee
                     for SIGIR2020 and SIGIR2022 and served as an Area Chair, Senior PC member, or PC member for
                     numerous key conferences such as SIGIR, WWW, WSDM, NeurIPS, EMNLP, AAAI, and IJCAI. --> </p>

